description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This is an exciting opportunity to advance in a dynamic Podiatry team into a Band 6 post based in the York team.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The role is under Harrogate and District NHS Foundation Trust that provides Podiatry Services to the whole of North Yorkshire and York. This covers approximately 3200 square miles and is provided from around 65 clinical locations.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The service is managed in 4 locality based teams.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Due to recent relocation of a current Podiatrist we are recruiting to a Band 6 position. The York team consists of 24 Podiatrists, supported by 3 Assistants, providing services to 13 clinical locations in this area.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Applicants must have 2 years clinical experience post-graduation. Good clinical skills, time management and organisational skills are critical to this role. You should have the ability to work on your own and as part of a team. There will be the potential to rotate through Biomechanics and High Risk clinics.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post is accountable to the Podiatry Team Lead for York.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This role will be based in the York Locality but may require cross cover of other localities in the future. As such a car owner or ability to travel is essential.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For more information please contact Laura Kirk - Podiatry Team Lead on 07733 300 116 or at laura.kirk1@nhs.net&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
